# AgentID Project Documentation

> Repo: `Vishal4742/agentid-kya-solana`
> Date: March 22, 2026
> Program ID (devnet target): `Gv35udP7tnnVcNiCMLKYeyjx1rfkeos4e6cXsFGr4tcF`

## Overview

AgentID is a Solana-based KYA protocol for AI agents. The current implementation centers on:

- `AgentIdentity` PDAs for on-chain identity
- on-chain capability flags and verification levels
- `AgentAction` PDAs for action logging
- oracle-driven reputation updates
- treasury instructions for agent-controlled spending limits
- a TypeScript SDK and ELIZA plugin that build locally against the current IDL

The repo is beyond prototype stage, but it is not yet production-ready.

## What Is Implemented

### Backend / Anchor program

- `register_agent`
- `update_capabilities`
- `log_action`
- `rate_agent`
- `verify_agent`
- `update_reputation`
- `init_config`
- treasury instructions for initialize, deposit, spending-limit updates, pause, and autonomous payment

Current reality:

- `register_agent` creates the identity account and leaves `credential_nft` unset
- Bubblegum CPI minting is not implemented yet
- `anchor test` passes locally for the current contract test suite

### Frontend

- Wallet integration with Phantom and Solflare
- Real program reads on `/agents`, `/verify`, `/dashboard`, and `/agent/:id`
- Registration flow wired to the Anchor program
- Treasury actions wired to the current IDL
- Docs page routed in the app

Current gaps:

- Landing page still uses `MOCK_AGENTS` in the live agents section
- cNFT credential display is present, but most accounts will not have a real credential yet

### SDK and plugin

- `packages/sdk` builds locally
- `packages/eliza-plugin` builds locally
- SDK methods are aligned with the current IDL for registration, logging, identity decoding, and helper verification

Current gaps:

- npm publication/release flow is not set up
- treasury/x402 flows are not exposed from the SDK yet

### Oracle

- Node/Express service exists in `backend/oracle`
- webhook auth is enforced
- webhook-triggered and hourly reputation recalculation are implemented
- the oracle writes updated scores on-chain through `update_reputation`

Current gaps:

- score inputs still depend on contract surfaces that need additional hardening
- tx-volume scoring is still effectively zero

### x402 / payment gateway

- middleware exists in `backend/x402`
- it verifies confirmed devnet USDC inflow to the target treasury
- it rejects replay of already-consumed signatures in memory

Current gaps:

- replay protection is not persisted across process restarts
- full production settlement/accounting flow is still pending

## Current Status by Area

| Area | Status |
|---|---|
| Identity registry | Buildable and working locally |
| Reputation engine | Implemented, but not fully hardened |
| Treasury layer | Partially implemented |
| Frontend | Feature-rich, mostly wired |
| SDK / ELIZA plugin | Buildable, not yet published |
| Bubblegum cNFT mint | Not implemented |
| India compliance backend | Partial |
| Mainnet readiness | Not ready |

## Known Important Gaps

- Bubblegum CPI and soul-bound cNFT minting are still pending
- some security hardening is still required before public deployment
- x402 is improved from placeholder status, but it is not complete production payment infrastructure
- the devnet deployment should be checked against the latest local code before treating the shipped IDL as the live deployed contract

## Recommended Read Order

- `MASTER_BUILD_GUIDE.md` for the high-level build log and current phase status
- `frontend/README.md` for frontend setup and UI status
- `packages/sdk/README.md` for the current SDK interface
- `packages/eliza-plugin/README.md` for plugin scope and limits
- `backend/oracle/README.md` for oracle runtime details
